The paper deals with estimating a person's attention level from visual cues, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning for attention level estimation, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and smart home systems, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
